<h1>Breakpoints</h1>
<p>
	Support for multiple breakpoints is vital for proper display of content across various browser sizes.
	While historically our main audience has come through on desktop, mobile viewing of Fandom's content has surpassed
	desktop traffic. Breakpoints allow for the proper display of content and advertising across devices.
	Design and engineering should create with responsiveness in mind, planning for multiple breakpoints.
</p>
<p>
	Fandom Design System uses <b>Mobile-first</b> approach.<br/>
	To set breakpoints pick one of variables from table below and use it in <code>@media</code> query in scss file.
</p>
<p>
	<img src="/images/breakpoints.png" class="breakpoints-visualisation">
</p>

<section>
	<h2 id="variables">Variables</h2>
	<table class="breakpoints-table">
		<tr class="breakpoints-table__header">
			<th>Breakpoint</th>
			<th>Variable</th>
			<th>Min</th>
			<th>Max</th>
		</tr>

		<tr>
			<td rowspan="2">Breakpoint S</td>
			<td><code class="format-code">$breakpoint-s-up</code></td>
			<td>0</td>
			<td>max</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td><code class="format-code">$breakpoint-s-only</code></td>
			<td>0</td>
			<td>767</td>
		</tr>

		<tr>
			<td rowspan="2">Breakpoint M</td>
			<td><code class="format-code">$breakpoint-m-up</code></td>
			<td>768</td>
			<td>max</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td><code class="format-code">$breakpoint-m-only</code></td>
			<td>768</td>
			<td>1023</td>
		</tr>

		<tr>
			<td rowspan="3">Breakpoint L</td>
			<td><code class="format-code">$breakpoint-l-down</code></td>
			<td>0</td>
			<td>1083</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td><code class="format-code">$breakpoint-l-up</code></td>
			<td>1024</td>
			<td>max</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td><code class="format-code">$breakpoint-l-only</code></td>
			<td>1024</td>
			<td>1083</td>
		</tr>

		<tr>
			<td rowspan="2">Breakpoint XL</td>
			<td><code class="format-code">$breakpoint-xl-up</code></td>
			<td>1084</td>
			<td>max</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td><code class="format-code">$breakpoint-xl-only</code></td>
			<td>1084</td>
			<td>1595</td>
		</tr>

		<tr>
			<td>Breakpoint XXL</td>
			<td><code class="format-code">$breakpoint-xxl-up</code></td>
			<td>1596</td>
			<td>max</td>
		</tr>
	</table>
</section>

<section>
	<h2>Example usage:</h2>
	{{#code-sample language='scss'}}
.example {
	width: 300px;

	.extra-content {
		display: none;
	}

	@media #{$breakpoint-m-up} {
		width: 700px;

		.extra-content {
			display: block;
		}
	}
}
	{{/code-sample}}
</section>
